name: Mom's Zucchini Pancakes
author: Suefood
summary: I am 'Mom' and I have been making these for years. My whole family just loves them. Serve with a small dollop of sour cream. They go fast!
ingredients: ¼ cup vegetable oil, or as needed
directions: Blot grated zucchini with paper towels to remove moisture
Stir zucchini, eggs, and onion in a large bowl
Mix flour, Parmesan cheese, baking powder, salt, and oregano in a separate bowl; stir mixture into zucchini until batter is just moistened
Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat
Drop rounded spoonfuls of zucchini batter into hot oil; pan fry until golden, 2 to 3 minutes per side
Drain pancakes on a paper towel-lined plate
